task.action:
Rewrite `src/components/shared/TagInput.tsx` with these changes (keep the same props interface):

**Layout change — inline pills:**
1. Replace the current two-section layout (pills above, input below) with a single container:
   ```tsx
   <div
     className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1 rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-3 py-1.5 text-sm ring-offset-background focus-within:outline-none focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-ring focus-within:ring-offset-2 min-h-[36px] cursor-text"
     onClick={() => inputRef.current?.focus()}
   >
     {/* Badge pills inline */}
     {selectedTags.map(tag => (
       <Badge key={tag.id} variant="secondary" className="flex items-center gap-1 pr-1 shrink-0">
         <span className="inline-block h-2 w-2 rounded-full flex-shrink-0" style={{ backgroundColor: tag.color }} />
         <span>{tag.name}</span>
         {!disabled && (
           <button type="button" onClick={(e) => { e.stopPropagation(); handleRemove(tag.id); }}
             className="ml-0.5 rounded-full hover:bg-muted-foreground/20 p-0.5" aria-label={`Remove ${tag.name}`}>
             <X className="h-3 w-3" />
           </button>
         )}
       </Badge>
     ))}
     {/* Bare input — no border, no ring */}
     {!atLimit && !disabled && (
       <input
         ref={inputRef}
         value={inputValue}
         onChange={handleInputChange}
         onKeyDown={handleKeyDown}
         onFocus={handleFocus}
         onBlur={handleBlur}
         placeholder={selectedTags.length === 0 ? "Add tags..." : ""}
         className="flex-1 min-w-[80px] bg-transparent outline-none placeholder:text-muted-foreground text-sm"
       />
     )}
   </div>
   ```
2. Wrap the entire container div in `PopoverAnchor asChild` so the dropdown anchors to the full container.
3. Remove the old `` import since we're using a bare `` element now.

**Focus fix:**
4. Replace `onFocus={() => setOpen(true)}` with:
   ```tsx
   const handleFocus = () => {
     const hasUnselectedTags = tags.some(t => !selectedTagIds.includes(t.id));
     setOpen(hasUnselectedTags);
   };
   ```
   This only opens the dropdown on focus if there are existing unselected tags to suggest.

5. Keep `onBlur` as `() => setTimeout(() => setOpen(false), 150)`.

**Enter key fix:**
6. Replace the `handleKeyDown` Enter logic with correct priority:
   ```tsx
   if (e.key === "Enter") {
     e.preventDefault();
     const trimmed = inputValue.trim();
     if (!trimmed) return;

     if (exactMatch) {
       // Exact match — select existing tag
       const matchingTag = filteredTags.find(
         t => t.name.toLowerCase() === trimmed.toLowerCase()
       ) || tags.find(t => t.name.toLowerCase() === trimmed.toLowerCase());
       if (matchingTag && !selectedTagIds.includes(matchingTag.id)) {
         handleSelect(matchingTag.id);
       }
     } else {
       // No exact match — create new tag
       handleCreate();
     }
   }
   ```

**Other adjustments:**
7. Change `handleInputChange` to always open the dropdown when text is present:
   ```tsx
   const handleInputChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) => {
     setInputValue(e.target.value);
     if (e.target.value.length > 0) {
       setOpen(true);
     }
   };
   ```

8. Keep the `atLimit` message and disabled state logic unchanged.
9. The `Popover` wraps around the entire component (container + popover content), NOT just the input.
